=== DOCUMENTATION FOR TARGET: HSIOWRAP ===

<reggrp_short_dscr>:
SYNC_ETH Configuration Registers
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Recovered Clock Configuration
------------------------------
<reg_public_text>:
This register is replicated once per recovered clock destination. Replications 0-3 are GPIO mapped recovered clocks 0 though 3. Replications 4-7 are SD10G mapped recovered clocks.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set to enable recovered clock generation. 
Bit is also used to enable corresponding GPIO pad.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disable (high-impedance)
1: Enable (output recovered clock)
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Select recovered clock divider.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Divide clock by 2
1: Divide clock by 4
2: Divide clock by 8
3: Divide clock by 16
4: Divide clock by 5
5: Divide clock by 25
6: No clock dividing
7: Reserved
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Select recovered clock source.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0-32: Select SD 0 through 32 recovered RX data clock
33: Select AUX1 clock from LCPLL1 reference
34: Select AUX2 clock from LCPLL1 reference
35: Select AUX3 clock from LCPLL1 reference
36: Select AUX4 clock from LCPLL1 reference
Other values are reserved.
------------------------------
<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Registers for accessing the GPIO pad cell configuration
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
GPIO pad cell configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Enable pull down resistor on GPIO inputs. Should not be set to '1' when G_PU is '1'
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Enable pull up resistor on GPIO inputs. Should not be set to '1' when G_PD is '1'
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Enable schmitt trigger function on GPIO inputs
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Controls the drive strength of GPIO outputs
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: minimum 6mA drive strength
1: minimum 10mA drive strength
2: minimum 14mA drive strength
3: minimum 18mA drive strength
------------------------------
<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Temperature sensor control
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
Controls the temperature sensor readout
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Temperature Sensor Configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
The number of system clock cycles in one 1us. 

This is used to generated the temperature sensor clock signal (CLK.)  The frequency of CLK must be higher than 0.75Mhz and lower than 2Mhz.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Reserved, must set to its default value.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Power up delay. The unit is number of sensor CLK cycles. See: CLK_CYCLES_1US

Default value corresponds to a 50us delay, which is the minimum required value.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set this bit to start a temperature sample cycle. This is only used if continuous sampling is disabled.

Procedure:
Set START_CAPTURE to 1
Wait until hardware clears START_CAPTURE 

Read temperature from TEMP_SENSOR_STAT.TEMP
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set this field to enable continuous sampling of temperature. 

The latest sample value will be available in TEMP_SENSOR_STAT.TEMP
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set this field to enable sampling of temperature. 

The sensor will be taken out of power down mode and the temperature sampling is stared when SAMPLE_ENA is set to 1
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Temperature Sensor Status
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This field is set when valid temperature data is available in TEMP_SENSOR_STAT.TEMP
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Temperature data readout This field is valid when TEMP_SENSOR_STAT.TEMP_VALID is set. This field is continually updated while the temperature sensor is enabled. 

See TEMP_SENSOR_CFG.SAMPLE_ENA for more information.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
Temp(C) = TEMP_SENSOR_STAT.TEMP / 4096 * 352.2 - 109.4
------------------------------
